<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-28T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="667" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">894.5151/247: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-28T23:00:00+09:00">July 28,
                                1941—11 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received July 28—11:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1111. Embassy’s 1108, July 28, 8 p.m.,<note n="11" xml:id="d667fn11">Not
                            printed.</note> numbered paragraph 4. The attention of the Department is
                        called to the fact that, whereas the American Government’s order freezing
                        Japanese assets restricts monthly expenditures of Japanese nationals to
                        $500, the Japanese ordinance provides for a sum of only 500 yen.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>